command: The keyboard shortcut that the user presses.
keywords: Keywords describing the function of the keyboard shortcut.
usagePriority:
The chance of this key being used.
                    For example, 1 represents the most used key, 2 is the
                    second most used key, and so on.
operatingSystem: The operating system that this command is used in.
application: The application that this command is used in.

action: Lock Mac Screen/Put Mac to sleep
keywords: lock mac screen sleep put to

keywords: send to trash delete file item
